results.name: Number of caps (also clutter partitions) of clutters (connected antichains) spanning n vertices.
comment: A kernel of a clutter is the restriction of the edge set to all edges contained within some connected vertex set. A clutter partition is a set partition of the edge set using kernels.
link: Gus Wiseman, Every Clutter Is a Tree of Blobs, The Mathematica Journal, Vol. 19, 2017.
Gus Wiseman, All clutter partitions of non-isomorphic clutters on 4 vertices.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Aug 02 2018
